cui_name: Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer - Adenocarcinoma Type
reasoning: NSCLC adenocarcinoma is the most common histological type. Global incidence approximately 16-17 per 100k. Data from GLOBOCAN 2005 and international cancer registries show significant variation by geographic region and smoking prevalence.
source: Parkin DM et al. (2005). Global cancer statistics, 2002. CA Cancer J Clin. 55(2):74-108
